<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">I hope this email finds you well. I am writing to inform you of a number of steps that we are taking in our ongoing cycle of school improvement in relation to our management of behaviour, encouragement of high expectations and reward.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">As you are no doubt aware we have a range of both formal and informal ways in which we celebrate success and encourage positive behaviour including awarding merits, the Awesome Achiever Award, weekly recognition emails and the Excellence Award. We also have a behaviour policy that aims to establish acceptable patterns of behaviour and to encourage pupils to develop a sense of responsibility, self-respect and a respect for other people, property and the environment by addressing behaviour when it falls short of expectation. To make our approach clearer to parents and to further emphasise the positives we will be taking the following steps by the end of term:</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">1. Students will no longer be required to carry conduct cards as we move to an electronic system for monitoring behaviour and rewards where appropriate.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">2. We will be working directly with students to develop an agreed Student Code of Conduct.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">3. We will look at other good schoolâ€™s policies in this area as we continue to develop a policy that works for our context.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">4. We will be reviewing and then combining our rewards and behaviour policies into one document that we will publish to the community on our website in early January.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">We hope that the aforementioned steps will help provide greater clarity about our approach in this important area.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Kind regards,</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Matthew Gilberthorpe</span></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Head of Secondary&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br><br></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" 